    "Then, we specifically selected papers that have question marks in their titles to build the QA dataset.",
    "This is because we can automatically obtain natural scholarly questions, and the corresponding answer is usually found within the abstract or the main content of the paper.",
    "By focusing on papers with question marks in their titles, we aim to capture a diverse set of research questions that are directly relevant to the field of chemistry.",
    "This approach allows us to construct a dataset that is rich in domain-specific questions and answers, providing a valuable resource for training and evaluating question-answering models in the scientific domain.",
    "In this work, we employ a multi-choice setting, where the questions are answered with 'yes', 'no', or 'maybe'."
